To ensure that noise can be effectively separated from the high-frequency detail to the detail layer, global noise estimation was implemented. In a static environment, the noise model is Gaussian noise, which can characterize the statistical properties of multiple random noise. However, under dynamic light conditions, the noise properties become more complex. In particular, when the light intensity changes dramatically, it may lead to a significant increase in salt and pepper noise, which appears as random bright or dark spots in the image, whose statistical properties are significantly different from Gaussian noise. To meet this challenge, a noise (

